# Redeploy bundle after notebook changes

When you edit any file under `notebooks/` (e.g. `sharepoint_transfer.py`), **redeploy the Databricks Asset Bundle** so the `sharepoint-transfer` job runs the updated code.

Run from the project root:

```bash
databricks bundle deploy
```

Use the default target (dev) unless the user specifies another. This ensures the job definition and notebook code on the workspace stay in sync with the repo.
